---
title: Baked Beef & Feta Wraps with a Cucumber Salad
description: Chef Jesse has seasoned the beef mince filling in this recipe with paprika, cumin, adding red peppers, carrots and creamy feta for added layers of texture. Baked until crispy - we recommend serving everything up in the middle of your table and getting everyone to tuck in. Enjoy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/spicy-beef-wrap-598de63c-8f0fb39f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/spicy-beef-wrap-5bd1e595ae08b507fd4fbcc2-023b74f9.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/spicy-beef-wrap-5bd1e595ae08b507fd4fbcc2
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: Middle Eastern
nutrition:
  calories: 759 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 43 g
  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 703
---

Preheat the oven to 200 degrees. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{}. Cook stirring occasionally until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(diced) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the onion to the beef and fry until softened and starting to colour, stirring often, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @ground cumin{2%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp}. Cook until fragrant, ~{2%minutes}. Pour in the @tomato passata{1%250g jar} and @water{100%ml} and stir well. Bring to the boil, then reduce heat to simmer. Cook until thick and tomatoey, ~{10%minutes}. When ready, stir in half the @coriander{1/2}(chopped, plus 1/2 for salad), season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste and keep to one side.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Roughly chop the remaining coriander (stalks and all). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim and grate the @carrot{1}(grated) (no need to peel). Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g}. Heat a splash of oil in another frying pan on high heat. Add the pepper and fry till soft, ~{5%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Lightly oil a large #baking tray{}.

> Chef Jesse has seasoned the beef mince filling in this recipe with paprika, cumin, adding red peppers, carrots and creamy feta for added layers of texture.

Lay a @super soft tortilla{1} on a #cutting board{}. Spoon 2-3 tbsp of the beef mix down the middle of the tortilla (leaving some space at each end). Pop a few slices of pepper on top then sprinkle on some carrot. Pop a little crumbled feta inside (save some for the top!), then fold the two short ends in, over the top of the filling followed by the two longer sides, like wrapping a present! You may have more filling than you need, just serve it along side at the end!

Transfer the wrap to your baking tray, folded side down. Repeat with the other @super soft tortillas{3}. Drizzle over a little more oil and gently rub over the top of the wraps. Crumble any remaining feta over the top and bake on the top shelf of the oven until lightly coloured and turning crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{1/2}(chopped), quarter lengthways, then chop widthways into small pieces. Pop into a #bowl{}. Mix in the remaining coriander, a squeeze of lime, a pinch of lime zest, a drizzle of @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste. Serve the wraps with the cucumber salad (and any spare lime wedges!) on the side. Enjoy!